07:00.976 --> 07:02.043
Good morning!

07:03.691 --> 07:06.158
Looks like we got us a nice day, huh?

07:09.356 --> 07:11.323
Are you, by any chance,
the welcoming committee?

07:11.843 --> 07:12.876
I ain't no committee.

07:13.360 --> 07:15.827
Still, it was nice of you to get
up so early and come down here.

07:16.149 --> 07:17.482
I always gets up early.

07:17.494 --> 07:19.894
Me, too. I'm afraid
I'll miss somethin'.

07:21.088 --> 07:22.688
I guess I oughta
introduce myself.

07:23.195 --> 07:24.128
I knows who you are.

07:25.267 --> 07:28.000
Okay.
Think it's gonna rain?

07:28.641 --> 07:29.808
Don't rain much this time of year.

07:31.496 --> 07:33.830
Well, I'm beginning to
run out of pleasantries.

07:34.670 --> 07:36.670
So if you'll just point me
in the direction to town...

07:49.814 --> 07:50.814
Good morning!

07:51.996 --> 07:52.996
Good morning.

07:54.742 --> 07:58.142
- I'm the new schoolteacher.
- Your hair is pretty long.

07:59.054 --> 08:03.154
- I'm a let it grow 'til the war's over.
- It's liable to reach your ass, son.

08:03.419 --> 08:05.452
Let's hope not.
Which way is the school, mister?

08:05.769 --> 08:07.802
If you're here to teach,
I reckon you can read.

08:51.588 --> 08:53.088
Welcome to Yamacraw Island.

08:54.445 --> 08:55.678
Welcome overseas.

08:56.346 --> 08:57.913
Thank you, ma'am.
It's great to be here.

08:57.960 --> 08:59.460
Don't speak too quickly.

09:00.195 --> 09:02.162
You're in a snake pit, son.

09:02.177 --> 09:04.944
And them snakes are gonna
start snappin' at your toes.

09:05.393 --> 09:07.260
I'm Mrs. Scott.
I'm the principal.

09:08.236 --> 09:11.503
- Pat Conroy.
- Do you mind working for a woman?

09:11.866 --> 09:14.666
No, ma'am. My father did it before
me and his father before him.

09:15.286 --> 09:17.419
Do you mind working
for a black woman?

09:19.000 --> 09:20.000
I'm here.

09:22.888 --> 09:25.621
Treat your babies stern,
treat 'em tough.

09:26.593 --> 09:30.793
Step on 'em. Step on 'em every
day when they get out of line.

09:30.817 --> 09:33.617
Put your foot on them
and keep it there.

09:34.812 --> 09:36.945
I know colored people
better than you do.

09:38.493 --> 09:42.293
If you have any trouble,
Mama Scott will be right next door.

09:43.186 --> 09:44.186
I'll holler.

09:46.605 --> 09:49.705
Here are the babies now.
Yours is the fifth grade to eighth.

11:53.265 --> 11:56.198
- Good morning, babies.
- Good morning.

11:57.123 --> 12:01.123
Uh, babies.
I know you got vocal cords.

12:01.139 --> 12:02.405
Let me hear you use 'em.

12:02.467 --> 12:05.467
Let me hear you say, "Good
morning", like you mean it.

12:05.794 --> 12:06.994
Good morning!

12:11.686 --> 12:15.686
Most of you are slow.
All of us know that.

12:15.793 --> 12:16.793
You don't think good.

12:18.063 --> 12:21.463
That's because you're just lazy.

12:21.867 --> 12:25.067
Lazy.
Lazy!

12:25.107 --> 12:28.474
And lazy people
can't get ahead in life.

12:28.808 --> 12:31.908
But you can learn if you work.

12:32.556 --> 12:36.089
Work, work, work,
work, work!

12:39.443 --> 12:44.076
I now have the privilege of
introducing Mr. Patroy to the class.

12:45.534 --> 12:49.834
Mr. Patroy is so good to
come over here this spring

12:50.580 --> 12:53.180
and take the place
of our Mrs. Frost

12:53.450 --> 12:57.116
who's gone to have her
gall bladder taken out.

12:58.713 --> 13:02.680
We are thankful that the Lord
brought Mr. Patroy to us.

13:09.898 --> 13:11.998
That's enough!
Now, I don't wanna hear no more!

13:12.218 --> 13:13.218
I said, quiet!

13:18.186 --> 13:21.519
I'm now going to turn you
babies over to Mr. Patroy.

13:23.011 --> 13:24.011
You're his

13:25.556 --> 13:26.556
and he's yours.

13:37.042 --> 13:39.275
I want y'all to take a
real long look at me.

13:44.491 --> 13:46.291
That shouldnâ€™t be any hardship

13:47.315 --> 13:48.649
'cause I'm handsome.

13:53.355 --> 13:54.355
Huh.

13:54.953 --> 13:58.286
A thousand years of Irish inbreeding
have produced these fine features.

13:58.764 --> 14:01.664
This pug nose,
this pugnacious jaw.

14:02.907 --> 14:07.107
Moreover, I have a penetrating wit,
a fanciful imagination,

14:07.155 --> 14:09.055
and my eyes are almost
as blue as Paul Newman's.

14:09.445 --> 14:10.945
I am your teacher!

14:11.108 --> 14:13.208
- He crazy.
- Crazy.

14:14.186 --> 14:15.186
As a loon.

14:15.419 --> 14:17.419
- What're you talkin' about?
- What're you sayin'?

14:17.805 --> 14:18.705
Never mind.

14:19.447 --> 14:21.247
Haul your chairs up
around me right over here.

14:21.290 --> 14:22.590
Just set 'em up around me here.

14:24.158 --> 14:25.491
Here, I'll get that for you.

14:28.081 --> 14:29.081
Let's get close.

14:29.907 --> 14:31.240
Everybody move, now. C'mon.

14:32.015 --> 14:34.549
Get as close as you can.
Hey, what're you talkin' about?

14:35.631 --> 14:36.631
That's good.

14:37.090 --> 14:38.457
You wanna sit on
that table there?

14:38.586 --> 14:39.586
Young man, go ahead.

14:45.421 --> 14:46.421
That's better.

14:47.062 --> 14:48.328
Let's start with my name.

14:48.334 --> 14:50.468
Various people are screwin' it up.
It's a swell name.

14:50.500 --> 14:55.000
It belonged to a bartender, a minister,
a classic scholar, and a Burlesque queen.

14:55.357 --> 14:56.357
It's Conroy.

14:56.837 --> 14:59.370
Not Patroy. Pat Conroy.
Let me hear it!

15:06.159 --> 15:07.159
You!

15:08.408 --> 15:09.874
- Me?
- Yeah, you.

15:11.269 --> 15:14.769
Con...rack.

15:15.386 --> 15:16.286
What?

15:16.648 --> 15:19.348
Con...rack.

15:19.749 --> 15:22.149
Close, but not close enough.
Conroy!

15:22.766 --> 15:24.899
Boy, ploy, toy, joy.

15:25.918 --> 15:26.918
You try.

15:29.520 --> 15:33.020
Con...rack.

15:33.799 --> 15:36.399
Take a big bite out of it.
Try to get your mouth around it.

15:37.332 --> 15:39.032
Pretend you got a tennis
ball stuck in there.

15:39.900 --> 15:42.200
Oy.
Conroy.

15:42.595 --> 15:43.628
C'mon, everybody try it.

15:43.778 --> 15:47.878
Oy, oy. C'mon.
Oy, oy.

15:48.193 --> 15:51.593
Oy.
Oy, oy.

15:52.240 --> 15:54.440
Oy.
All right, you try it.

15:56.172 --> 15:57.172
Con...

15:59.577 --> 16:00.577
...rack.

16:01.738 --> 16:04.971
You know somethin'?
I'm beginning to like the sound of it.

16:06.160 --> 16:09.227
What country do we live in, gang?
Everybody tell me at once.

16:15.575 --> 16:16.575
Gang?

16:24.823 --> 16:27.523
What is the name of this grand old
red, white and blue country of ours?

16:28.631 --> 16:31.998
The place where we live, land of the
free and the home of the brave?

16:39.580 --> 16:41.580
Does anyone know what
country we live in?

16:51.859 --> 16:53.626
Honey, how much is two and two?

17:20.904 --> 17:22.471
How many fingers have
I got raised up here?

17:27.777 --> 17:28.777
Eight?

17:30.146 --> 17:32.013
You only missed it by two.
Try again.

17:36.747 --> 17:37.747
Two?

17:38.202 --> 17:41.602
I'll tell you what. Start at this first
finger and count to the last one.

17:48.327 --> 17:49.327
Five.

18:00.612 --> 18:01.612
Mrs. Scott!

18:01.642 --> 18:03.775
I just now completed my
first day in your school.

18:04.672 --> 18:06.405
The hair on the back of
my neck is standing up.

18:06.465 --> 18:09.765
Mrs. Scott, seven of my students
cannot recite the alphabet.

18:10.127 --> 18:11.693
Three children cannot
spell their names.

18:11.751 --> 18:16.051
Eighteen children do not know we're
fighting a war in Southeast Asia!

18:17.366 --> 18:18.599
Eighteen children never heard of Asia.

18:18.688 --> 18:21.188
One child thinks the Earth is flat.
The seventeen others agreed with him.

18:21.925 --> 18:24.725
Two children don't know how old they are,
five children don't know their birthdays.

18:24.764 --> 18:28.130
Four children can't count to ten.
The four oldest in the class

18:28.293 --> 18:30.993
think the Civil War was fought
between the Germans and the Japanese!

18:31.387 --> 18:34.987
None of them know who Willie Mays or
George Washington or Sidney Poitier is.

18:35.250 --> 18:38.617
Not one of them's ever been to a movie or stood
on top of the hill or ridden on a city bus.

18:38.637 --> 18:40.437
Those kids don't know crap!

18:42.158 --> 18:44.691
Remember what I told you
about colored children?

18:45.484 --> 18:49.151
They are slow. They need the whip.
They understand the whip.

18:50.859 --> 18:52.892
We're off the old plantation, Mrs. Scott.

18:53.610 --> 18:56.477
And I'll be goddamned if you're
gonna turn me into an overseer.

19:13.737 --> 19:16.804
How's it goin' today?
Caught any big ones?

19:17.058 --> 19:19.058
You've gotta stick with it.

19:30.856 --> 19:32.590
You the new schoolteacher?

19:38.445 --> 19:39.445
Yes, ma'am.

19:40.096 --> 19:43.329
- I'm the midwife over here.
- Oh.

19:43.767 --> 19:46.734
All these children on
this island my children.

19:47.518 --> 19:51.918
I take 'em out of their mothers.
I see 'em when they first be born.

19:52.319 --> 19:53.919
I bring 'em into this Earth.

19:54.949 --> 19:57.749
- Now you got 'em.
- Yes, ma'am.

19:58.090 --> 20:00.557
Treat 'em right,
and they'll do good for you.

20:02.153 --> 20:06.086
- Yes, ma'am.
- Treat 'em right, and they'll do good for you.

20:35.325 --> 20:36.325
Hey!

20:48.884 --> 20:49.884
Hey!

20:50.573 --> 20:51.573
Huh!

20:53.039 --> 20:54.039
Sit down.

21:29.082 --> 21:30.082
Top Cat Jones!

21:30.359 --> 21:31.726
Are you out of your mind?

21:31.727 --> 21:34.627
Are you darin' to lift a finger
and lay it on our Mr. Patroy?

21:34.634 --> 21:36.134
Conroy, goddammit!

21:36.696 --> 21:37.696
Conrack hurts!

21:40.118 --> 21:45.218
It wa- It wasn't him. It was me.
I felt like a little wrestling this morning.

21:45.557 --> 21:49.490
Mr. Patroy, you have already lost
the respect of these children.

21:49.531 --> 21:53.831
You have lowered yourself in their eyes.
They need discipline, not fun time.

21:53.889 --> 21:58.156
- This school isn't any fun time, you know?
- I'm enjoying myself.

21:58.344 --> 22:01.244
Well, you take Dr. Medicine
here and you give that boy a dose.

22:01.474 --> 22:02.974
A good one,
one he'll remember.

22:03.171 --> 22:05.737
You got to remember we are
overseas, Mr. Patroy.

22:05.944 --> 22:07.644
And things are tough overseas!

22:23.135 --> 22:24.902
Okay, gang, everybody sit down.

22:29.376 --> 22:30.709
Y'all listen up now.

22:31.725 --> 22:33.892
That little horseplay was designed
to get those old eyelids open,

22:33.910 --> 22:36.110
get your blood pressure up,
get that gray matter perkin'.

22:46.262 --> 22:47.262
Today

22:48.447 --> 22:49.447
we're gonna have a filibuster.

22:49.460 --> 22:50.993
That's somethin' we do very
well here in the South.

22:51.109 --> 22:53.209
It means a talkathon.
I'm gonna talk, and you're gonna listen.

22:53.880 --> 22:56.747
Anybody has to go pee, do it now,
'cause we're gonna be at it all day.

23:01.067 --> 23:02.067
All right.

23:03.910 --> 23:06.777
I was born in Beaufort, South Carolina,
where I grew up and went to school.

23:06.812 --> 23:08.112
I was a bigoted little boy.

23:08.350 --> 23:11.616
Bigot, that's somebody with
a red neck and a small brain.

23:12.440 --> 23:14.940
And I went to an all-white,
male military college

23:15.012 --> 23:17.412
where I wore a uniform even
when I went to the latrine.

23:18.296 --> 23:19.496
That's the toilet.

23:21.241 --> 23:24.741
I ate a lotta grits,
smelled a lotta magnolias in my time.

23:25.943 --> 23:28.743
I went to the movies twice a week.
My favorite actor was Humphrey Bogart.

23:29.042 --> 23:32.109
He was my favorite 'cause he
never took any shit from anybody.

23:36.674 --> 23:38.074
I learned about books

23:39.459 --> 23:42.559
from the third baseman on my college
baseball team who read Milton.

23:43.445 --> 23:44.945
And I learned about sex

23:45.785 --> 23:47.652
from the girl next door to my house

23:47.860 --> 23:49.460
who read Havelock Ellis.

23:51.438 --> 23:53.438
I'm gonna be readin'
both of them to you.

23:55.858 --> 23:59.358
I drive a small yellow car called a Volkswagen,
manufactured in a country called Germany

23:59.826 --> 24:01.759
on a continent called Europe.

24:02.322 --> 24:05.355
I write bad poetry, I write great
letters to newspaper editors.

24:05.410 --> 24:08.710
I'm a hypochondriac, that's somebody who's
afraid he's dyin' every time he sneezes.

24:08.766 --> 24:11.966
I believe in love of all kinds.
Carnal, platonic,

24:12.377 --> 24:13.377
fraternal,

24:13.874 --> 24:14.874
maternal,

24:15.609 --> 24:16.609
religious.

24:20.339 --> 24:21.339
Goofin' off?

24:23.095 --> 24:24.628
Just gettin' my supper.

24:25.151 --> 24:26.351
How'd you like to get mine?

24:27.078 --> 24:28.078
What you mean?

24:28.361 --> 24:30.694
I need somebody to cook for me,
do the dishes, wash my clothes.

24:30.779 --> 24:32.779
I need a little lookin' after.

24:32.946 --> 24:35.979
- How much you gonna pay?
- How much you want?

24:37.076 --> 24:38.143
A dollar.

24:38.385 --> 24:41.485
- A week?
- No, man. A day.

24:42.622 --> 24:45.222
I guess I can afford that,
if I cut down on my beer.

24:46.143 --> 24:49.143
- All right, I'll give you a try.
- I take home the leftovers?

24:49.284 --> 24:51.884
If you're a good cook,
there won't be any.

25:11.382 --> 25:13.682
- You awake?
- I is now.

25:14.972 --> 25:18.838
- What did you eat for breakfast?
- Piece o' bread, Coca-Cola.

25:19.579 --> 25:23.379
Tomorrow, eat an egg. Eat two.
Protein gives you a slug of energy.

25:23.690 --> 25:25.690
I want everybody here slugged.

25:27.790 --> 25:29.024
What's all that racket?

25:29.079 --> 25:31.212
Reveille, Mrs. Scott.
Just a small reveille.

25:35.163 --> 25:36.313
Okay, gang.

25:36.338 --> 25:39.687
I'd like to have a word with your
babies, Mr. Patroy.

25:43.282 --> 25:44.282
Last night

25:45.576 --> 25:49.176
I found a puddle on one
of the seats in here.

25:50.666 --> 25:55.999
Now, babies, everybody has got to u-ri-nate.
Isn't that right?

25:56.533 --> 26:00.033
And ain't nothing wrong
with a man urinating.

26:01.858 --> 26:05.058
But you could ruin a
seat by urinating on it.

26:06.832 --> 26:10.566
All of us know that urine
is made out of ...?

26:11.243 --> 26:12.243
Acid.

26:13.328 --> 26:16.628
And acid can eat
right through a chair.

26:19.807 --> 26:21.707
There's plenty of weak
bladders in the world.

26:21.806 --> 26:27.706
The bladder is just like a muscle.
Some weak, some strong.

26:29.021 --> 26:35.147
Now, whoever that person is who wet the
chair, and he knows who he is,

26:36.135 --> 26:38.935
should stand up now and say,
"Mrs. Scott,

26:39.697 --> 26:42.731
I have a weak bladder,
and I am very sorry."

26:46.475 --> 26:48.808
Mrs. Scott, I have a weak
bladder, and I'm very sorry.

26:50.220 --> 26:52.860
Okay. A-all right. A-all right.

26:55.453 --> 26:56.453
What are you talking about?

26:57.319 --> 26:59.485
I was the last person sittin'
in that chair yesterday.

27:01.423 --> 27:05.156
Mr. Patroy, I got a right
side, and I got a wrong side.

27:05.374 --> 27:07.774
And you are getting
on the wrong one.

27:12.216 --> 27:13.216
Okay, gang.

27:13.911 --> 27:17.078
Everybody's gonna look good today,
everybody's gonna shine like the sun.

27:17.988 --> 27:20.721
Ronny, in your opinion,
who is the greatest man who ever lived?

27:23.124 --> 27:24.124
Jesus.

27:24.581 --> 27:26.181
All right, I'll buy that.
Now, somebody else.

27:26.893 --> 27:28.226
Who's the second greatest?

27:29.142 --> 27:30.142
Jesus Christ.

27:31.504 --> 27:34.171
They're one and the same,
Debbie, Jesus and Jesus Christ.

27:34.753 --> 27:37.553
Anybody wanna say a good
word for Moses or Buddha?

27:37.571 --> 27:39.471
- No!
- No? Okay.

27:40.285 --> 27:41.285
Let's go on.

27:41.674 --> 27:42.840
Who can name me an ocean?

27:44.028 --> 27:45.161
I'm gonna give you a hint:

27:45.251 --> 27:47.217
One of the oceans of the
world washes right up against

27:47.242 --> 27:49.708
the shores of our own
scenic Yamacraw Island.

27:49.962 --> 27:51.429
Oh, he mean the beach!

27:51.569 --> 27:54.469
What's beyond the beach? What's the name
given to that whole ocean out there?

27:54.822 --> 27:56.089
It's just the beach, man.

27:56.980 --> 27:58.680
Okay, it's the beach.

27:59.276 --> 28:01.609
But just for the record,
it's also called the Atlantic Ocean.

28:02.888 --> 28:05.788
- Have you ever heard it called that?
- No, we ain't, Conrack.

28:06.152 --> 28:08.552
Well, don't worry about it.
That kinda stuff is easy to learn.

28:08.768 --> 28:11.501
Just by rappin' about it,
we'll learn which ocean is off Yamacraw.

28:13.503 --> 28:16.536
All right. Veola!
What is the name of the ocean?

28:16.817 --> 28:17.817
Lantic Ocean.

28:17.847 --> 28:20.047
- Atlantic Ocean.
- Atlantic Ocean.

28:20.122 --> 28:23.022
- What ocean, everybody?
- Atlantic Ocean!

28:23.063 --> 28:26.863
- Are you sure it's the Atlantic Ocean?
- Yeah, we sure.

28:26.935 --> 28:29.402
Well, it's not. The real name of
the ocean is the Conroy Ocean.

28:29.482 --> 28:31.482
Oh, no.

28:32.069 --> 28:33.869
Yeah! Yeah, it's the truth!

28:34.761 --> 28:38.321
My great-great grandfather was Ferdinand
Conroy, a Spanish soldier of fortune

28:38.346 --> 28:42.185
who swam from Europe to North America,
a distance of fifteen million miles.

28:42.639 --> 28:45.839
Because of this singular and
extraordinary feat, from that day forward,

28:45.867 --> 28:47.534
it's been called the Conroy Ocean.

28:48.555 --> 28:50.555
- No.
- How do you know?

28:51.033 --> 28:53.166
Just think.
You said it was the Atlantic.

28:54.366 --> 28:57.166
- I'm a liar.
- Can't be. You's a teacher.

28:58.810 --> 29:01.743
Teachers lie all the time.

29:09.882 --> 29:10.882
All right now.

29:11.944 --> 29:13.744
The Lotus position of Yoga.

29:14.577 --> 29:19.177
Yoga is a discipline aimed at the
state of perfect spiritual insight

29:19.511 --> 29:20.511
and tranquility.

29:20.540 --> 29:22.207
- Lord, look at him.
- Hey!

29:22.723 --> 29:25.756
It's said to clear the mind

29:27.595 --> 29:30.228
and drain... drain the sinus.

29:41.794 --> 29:47.694
Gravity. A law first stated by Isaac Newton
and elaborated on by Johannes Kepler.

29:47.850 --> 29:49.883
- Isaac Newton!
- Isaac Newton!

29:49.978 --> 29:52.612
- Johannes Kepler!
- Johannes Kepler!

29:52.716 --> 29:54.183
- Gravity!
- Gravity!

29:54.575 --> 29:57.042
- Isaac Gravity!
- Isaac Gravity!

29:58.130 --> 29:59.130
All right now.

29:59.314 --> 30:03.614
Everybody brush down from the gum.
Down... down from the gum.

30:03.983 --> 30:07.916
Now up... up from the bottom,
up from the gum, from the bottom.

30:08.725 --> 30:10.858
Good. And now everybody...
spit!

30:12.940 --> 30:14.640
Try not to spit on the teacher!

30:24.682 --> 30:26.416
These are the worst biscuits I ever ate.

30:27.613 --> 30:29.013
And I've been in the army!

30:29.645 --> 30:31.112
You don't like 'em, don't eat 'em.

30:31.893 --> 30:33.993
- What's in 'em?
- Done my own recipe.

30:34.724 --> 30:37.124
So have I.
Come on in here.

30:46.432 --> 30:47.432
Here.

30:48.967 --> 30:52.700
- I don't cook fancy.
- You don't read fancy, either, do you?

30:53.159 --> 30:55.225
All right.
This word is "cup."

30:55.982 --> 30:57.315
"Two cups of flour."

30:57.651 --> 31:00.284
This word is "teaspoon".
One teaspoon of baking powder.

31:00.876 --> 31:03.076
This word is "pound".
A quarter pound of shortenin'.

